\section{Clinical Error Taxonomy}

Systematic qualitative analysis across all ten languages and three
experimental conditions identifies eight recurring error patterns.
Table~\ref{tab:error_taxonomy} summarises each type by mechanism,
affected conditions, clinical risk, and detectability without the
source dialogue. The categories are not mutually exclusive; a single
summary can exhibit multiple types simultaneously. The most dangerous
is \textbf{T3}~(entity bleed), because the fabricated content is
clinically accurate---it describes the demonstration patient, not the
test patient---and is therefore undetectable by a clinician reading
the summary alone. \textbf{T7} and \textbf{T8} are specific to the
translation pipeline; \textbf{T3} is exclusive to few-shot.
Illustrative examples for Telugu zero-shot, few-shot, and translation
outputs are provided in Appendix~\ref{sec:qualitative_appendix}.

